transcript: I used to beat myself up a lot about like I should be stronger I should be richer I should be whatever and so I'd be like I'm not X comma and that's okay and so that phrase actually started in my head because I started giving myself permission to give myself space it just started entering in my daily lexicon of things that I say and so that outward comma and that's okay is actually just a representation of like how I think to myself all the time in accepting current state rather than trying to create a discrepancy between where I am and where I want to be which then creates the tension of just why do I suck so much
